content: Highly recommend!
Not bad, but the color need to improve feel very solid.

A simple daily diary to help you keep track of various activities, foods, etc. & quickly search to compare how they made you feel. It's not a fancy app with sorting or reporting capabilities, but it has been very useful for quite some time now.
Ease to use, really like ability to set up several different categories.
So far so good. Using the app to keep a food diary for alzheimers family member. Simple to use can just write in details for each day with ability to edit and and details later on in the day.
Easy to use, very intuitive. No ads. Great app.
Super for tracking all health details. It is helping me figure out migraine triggers, including the weather.

This app is exactly what I wanted which was to record what I ate and any symptoms I had. You can edit, you can add the exact time. It has an activity option but I don't use this. I haven't tried the export option either but I'd recommend this app for doing what it says it'll do.

I tried to use this for calorie counting, I can I guess, I used the 
comments section for the calorie count of an item. it would be nice if 
adding up the daily calories was automatic.

7/2018 on Galaxy J7 Prime. Android Version 7. Still works fine. Can add and edit categories all except the first one which says "Uncategorized". Not a problem though. Just a note to developer.   Earlier review: Since I use this wonderful and simple app constantly I'm willing to beta test updates.         Galaxy Note 3
replyContent:
There's not currently a way to change the background color, but you should be able to choose new category colors. (It would've tried to automatically pick similar but darker ones, but it's not an exact science)
Can you please contact me over email with more detail on your issue with the categories screen and I'll try to sort it out quickly.

content:
nice and simple, no frills. exactly what i was looking for. app is 
stable...no crashing or locking up

Love it! Simple and easy to use, allows you to write your own ratings and 
comments for the day. A weekly overview of the ratings maybe would be nice 
so we can see what days we rated well

When copying over to another day the app shows everything copied over. You have to close and reopen to see the correct copied over item. Nowhere in app to give feedback hence this negative review. Very basic app which should be free

Really enjoying how simple and easy this app makes tracking my food and symptoms. Only thing that is holding me back from a 5 star rating is that I wish you could attach a photo to an entry. For example snap a photo of an ingredient list and attach it to a food entry.
Wasted Â£0.69. The diary tends to duplicate records, export to xls works fine but impossible to import.

Useless - not worth the $0.99 I paid. It seems like a really good idea - unfortunately it doesn't work correctly - I entered my meals, supplements, etc. on Day 1 - great - then I added items on Day 2 (some items were the same like coffee, others were different) - great - on Day 3 the app had duplicated everything I entered on day 2 into that day - when I deleted an item from Day 3 it deleted it from Day 2 - when I edit an item (like the time I had coffee) on Day 3 the app changed that item on all previous days - when I deleted everything on Day 3 (which deleted everything on Day 2 (unless it was also on Day 1) then I could reenter items on Day 2 and enter new items on Day 3 - editing any already existing items still changed them everywhere,-

This is the start of a framework for a good food diary app. Unfortunately it's missing fundemental forms for nutrients and ingredients tracking for diabetics and people with specific deficiencies. Can you please implement a recipe and ingredients form which has nutritional values and energy entries so we can create our own menus to choose from for food and drink? Also some way to print directly to A6/A5/A4 paper to create a printed food diary with nutritional breakdowns would be of great benefit. Currently everything needs to be entered manually and it's a pain to format and enter this complex data into a simple notes type system. Forms for recipes and nutrition would be much simpler and easier. Thanks.

I LOVE this app. I have IBS and it's important for me to track food as well as bowel movements. This format makes it really easy to go back and look at food patterns to determine what the trigger foods were.  Love that you can choose light or dark theme! Thanks!!!
replyContent: The dark theme is returning as an option in the next update (that I'm currently beta testing)

content: Seems simple and straightforward to use, but very annoying that the entries don't word wrap when viewing them.

Simple to use. Easy to export. Things  that would make this app perfect: 1. Automatically sync to Google Drive for backup and restore. 2. Day of the week also printed. 3. When exporting, app remember last day exported. 4. Choose multiple categories to print instead of just all or one category. Still love the app despite these shortcomings and have used for 4 months. Tried other apps but this is the most simple with all the features I need. Great for keeping track of food and symptoms.

On 12/27/17 I was diagnosed with stage 4 pancreatic cancer. After several days of crying we put together a plan and it includes this app. This is not a diet app or calorie counter. It is a plain and simple way to track exactly what you are eating when you exercise and just about anything else you want to track.  This app is so freeking simple to keep track of what I eat, do, or feel. No effort to learn at all!   If you have pain get a checkup. If you're sick get this app
Easy to use, love the ability to change categories colour and name them. Time and date entries are really good. Love this app

Love the simplicity of the app. 2 things :  Wish you could add a picture for each meal. I don't weigh food so a picture of the portion size is always a good reference when looking back. Please add the option to take photos to every log entry. Also would like to see a backup option or sync option with our google play account. I would hate to reformat my phone and lose every entry I made. Add these options and it would be a 5 star app!  Great work dev
It's not a comprehensive review - I tried the app but gave up, because the autocomplete wasn't working at all.

Old version was very responsive and easy to use. New interface is clunky and very slow to pull up records. The export features are nice, and the concept is good, wish it ran more smoothly. Tried reaching out to support but no response.
Simple and well designed
The interface is pretty good and is easy to enter data. Unfortunately it is local to the device where you enter the data so you can't use the same log on more than one device.

Functions really well as a simple food diary app, others wanted to many details and I ain't got time for that. I think you should also just be able to add pictures straight from your camera, incase you have something complex. The import/export option is the best, really good for people to be able to send their diary to GP/PT etc.
Dope and simple.  Just wanted to track what I eat without all the diet stuff and calorie tracking. Some healthy people just want to remember what we are eating. Please keep it simple.
Where's the instructions? Other (free) apps make more sense right away.

Can also be used for other purposes. Everything which should be noted for a period of time can be put in. Choose a different colour and you will easily find it again. For example the number of cigarettes you smoked today. Put time and comment in, and you will see, how many you smoked, when and under which circumstances you smoked more or less. - 19.06.2016 Prg has improved a lot. Absolutely superb now. Highly to recommend.
Changed my phone recently, and formatted the old device. Everything gone.
I can't believe I just paid for this dum A$$ app there's no instructions how to use it I don't know where to put or  keep my food diary it's just stupid!!!! do not install

Very happy I found this diary that made possible for me a lot to follow my dietologist's guidelines to write down everything I eat, when I go to toilet and when I exersice. Only problem is that it shows the foods you register one day on the next day as well. Then suddenly it fixes itself. But is frustrating  & confusing. Apart from this, I believe that it should also have a report option that devides the days in 5 segments, breakfast, brunch, lunch, afternoon snack, dinner. Apart from this, very good app!
Missing food item database and statistics

Its has a clock for the day but does not seem to be able to add a breakfast then a lunch then a dinner at different times. When I try to enter say lunch after breakfast it erases the breakfast and will only allow one entry. I wanted to keep track of my meals throughout the day. This does not seem to be able to do that.
I love this app! I would suggest allowing pictures to be added with the entry! It would be so much more fun and cool.
Simple and easy to use. I love that I can log in what food I eat and the time that I ate it so I can eat at the same times the next day.

The app is nice and easy to use. However, I expected to get more since app is not free. Current day is not set automatically in the morning, so I log to yesterday by mistake. It would also be good to have widget for quick add. Auto-backup is also missing.

It does exactly what I need, no extra garbage and no ads are a plus. Every day I have to stop the app in task manager as it goes a little buggy, listing all the previous day's entries under the new day. Edit: all of my other issues were operator error, its working great.
I like the app, but can't get import/export to work. Any ideas Geoff?
replyContent: The fix to the export issue should be rolling out now.

content: This app is great. It's simple and does everything I need it to do, no more, no less. Well worth the nominal price!
crashes all the time. I use this app everyday and the last version was great, how can I reverse?
replyContent: Please let me know what you're doing when it crashes over email (or submit the crash report), and I'll sort the issue out for you.

content: Was crashing but the new update seems to have worked, and the dark theme is back!

No unnecessary permissions: 5 stars for that alone! I use this to track food, medication, mood/stress level, and physical activity. It helped me figure out my migraines. Now I am using it to focus on healthier eating habits. Being able to export to a spreadsheet makes this invaluable. Thank you! Edit: Love the 2016 updates! Thank you :)

This app has crashed twice since last update, i keep adding items to the diary and then they disappear, it keeps moving them to other dates and then they magically appear again. Then it will move everything from previous date and copy current date. Very frustrating.                                          ***Edit---thabks for your continued replies. After the last update its gone back to displaying items on wrong date etc. Reinstall fixed first time but lost all my data. Am i going to have to do it again??
replyContent:
You shouldn't have to do it again.
Can you please contact me over email and I'll try to get this sorted out for you?

content: Exellent app!
replyContent: Sorry for the issues with the v2.0.0 release. The issue should be resolved with the v2.0.1 version that's out now.

content: That's probably not a great thing, but this Food Diary app is the best I've tried. It is perfect for tracking meals, pills, etc. Yes, even good for keeping track of the embarrassing stuff that comes along with IBS, Crohns, etc.        For those who had an issue with the last update it's working great after this latest version. By the way, it is always a better idea to contact the developer first before leaving a negative review. That's the best way to get issues resolved. Thanks for a great product!

TBQH I kinda preferred the old interface with the big enter button, but this is exactly what is looking for in a food logging app - it's a simple record without the sort of complexity other apps have, which I don't need.
Loved the app but after update doesn't work at all. Won't save entries and replacing yesterday's with what I try to input today. Want my money back or app fixed!!
replyContent: I apologize for the trouble. The latest update has caused some major issues for some users. I'm currently working on a fix for this, it should be ready in the next couple of days.

content: Decent app, wish it gave an option to allow photos to be added as well as just documentation

I'm highly upset with this update. It doesn't color code my catagories anymore. I'm a diabetic and I track my sugar levels, diabetic meds & insulin plus my meals. I hate the way it is now. Why can't it have been left alone. Now I got to try and find another simple app to use!! Thanks...
replyContent:
Could you please contact me over email with some more details about the issues with your category coloring (what color are things now, what they were before, etc)  and I'll try to address the issue quickly. 
I'm sorry for any inconvenience.

content: Nice UI upgrade :-)
Finally found what I was looking for.
It's working great and I'm very happy with it. I just wish it would sync across apps
Simple and effective. A suggestion: Feature to record quantity. Eg. Toast x 3

It's a useful app, but it'd be nice to have some things more. First of all: a back-up functionality (for example with google drive, dropbox, by Google or Facebook accounts, etc). Another useful tool to add to the app would be a plotter. Maybe a bar diagram or a cake plot are the best option but something to plot must be added!
I like the app, but I would love it if you add a whole month view for a quicker search and input data with keyboard.  good job . Thanks
Love it

I just installed this app and love it already. A feature where I can add a picture to an entry would be nice. This was exactly what i was looking for. Simple health tracking - no calorie counting which is just frustrating :) I would be curious to know what others use as categories.  Awesome app, well worth .99
Simple, not too complicated, works well

Very useful app. Great to categorise medicine and food etc. A couple of improvements I'd like to see are:  drop down screen allows you to add items you've typed before regardless of how you type.. For instance if you added 'baked potato' one day and then tried typing 'potato baked'. I would also like to be able to click into a food item I have and modify recepie ingredients, for instance if I cooked a recepie twice with one ingredient changed I wouldn't have to type the wholel list again. Thanks!! :-)
replyContent:
You should see some of these improvements in the latest update.
The drop down should search titles better, and the comment field should automatically fill in with the most recent entry with the same title.

content: Can you make the comment section bigger?  I like to describe how I felt during the day and what happened to figure why I over-ate if I did.  Love the app, otherwise!
I have entries from yesterday.  However, now they show up today even though their dates are from yesterday.  How can I keep entries within their entry dates?

When I had an iPhone,  I looked high and low for a simple food tracking app like this. I could never find one that suited my needs.  I was so excited to find it in the google play store! I love how it remembers your past entries and the categories they fit into.  My one wish is that I could enter the time using the keypad.  Sometimes I forget to add what I've been eating until later in the day,  and scrolling through the time is cumbersome.  Otherwise,  great work!
Simple & makes keeping track of what i eat soooo much easier..not alot of bells n whistle you DON'T need!!! And the black background is a JOY for my eyes! Ty devs!
I can track whatever I want and log the times, too.  Haven't customized categories, but probably will soon.
Open app, enter item you ate, save. Simple. Minimalistic.

First it deleted all of my Saturday entries once Sunday hit, then it began to tell me I had not bought the app and even after restarting, deleting, reinstalling, it still doesn't work. I would have asked for support but there is no visable means to ask for it, so all I can do is leave this review.
replyContent:
I apologize that the app didn't work out for you.
Your Saturday entries should have just been on the previous page once Sunday came around.
You shouldn't have seen the error about not having bought the app, but I could've sorted that out for you if you had contacted me via the email link on the Google Play page.

content: Really easy to use.  Also can email food guide to nutritionist if needed for tracking.

It deleted all my entries when I added a new category. I thought that was a bit messed up. Glad I only had a day's worth in there. Also glad it was only a buck. Great layout. Simple. Easy UI. But that quirk was a deal breaker. That simple fix would bump my review up to four stars.

Most of the apps out there are calorie trackers with (a limited) preset library of foods mainly catered to western world. I have been looking for a simple food/activity journal to track food intake daily and understand my eating habits (and correlation between time of the day and cravings). This app fits that requirement perfectly!
This app is great.  The ability to plug food in for the next day would be amazing!
Great journal and easily customizable!  I highly recommend!

Unless I am missing the lion's share of this app's functionality, it did not in any way give me closure on my food intolerances. As the app does little more than combine text entry fields with a calendar and a drop down of some relevant categories, I got tired of using it after 4 days. The worst part? I actually spent money on it :(
I have a hard time keeping a food journal. So far I like it. We'll see how it goes. :-)
not exactly what I needed. There are better free ones out there from people with intolerance
This app is easy and fun to use.  Very doable way to see what you really eat.  Wish it were avail for Apple

So far this app is easy to use and the export feature is very welcome.  It has all the features I need but if you're looking for calorie or points counting, you'll need to look elsewhere.  The ability to create your own categories is very useful as I am using these to track when I take medications and when I experience symptoms in addition to tracking food intake.  What would make this a 5-star rating from me would be the option to have previously entered items appear in the "Title" field as you start typing.  This would be espcially useful when combined with the export feature as you could then easily count the occurrences of items without having to account for variations in the way they were entered.  UPDATED: Sometime after typing this review, I noted that previously entred items started appearing.  No idea how or why, but it's working, so changed to 5 star rating.  And on a positive note, the developer promptly replied to my concern re: items not appearing, so obviously pays attention to the reviews made.  Unlike a lot of other developers out there!
replyContent:
Previously entered items should already appear in the title field after you've typed 3 characters.
If this is not working for you, feel free to contact me via email and we can find out why it's not currently working for you.

content: Very nice app, I use it daily and it is granular enough for my needs.  Would be nice if I could get a carriage return button in the title box when capturing details.  Other than that the app is great.

My husband just had a Whipple. With that comes a lot of changes in eating that are necessary. Foods that used to be OK no longer are and each person is different. This allows me to track what he is eating and when then also track any bad symptoms and when as well. My biggest wish would be ability to sync between devices. Even having to pay more that would be a highly valuable feature.
It is simple to use and keep track. I live the catagories to keep tracknof activity and health items too. How do you delete an item??
No calorie counter

It seems fine for what it actually does. I bought this because I was looking for a app where I could take a photo of my food because I do not write things down consistently and I somehow got it into my head that the app had this capability.  If you're like me this is not for you. Too bad because this is simple to use and I liked the privacy settings, but for me to consistently record something it has to be automatic or a pic.
I need to keep a food and mood diary and this appears that it will do the trick. Is there a way to change the color of a category if you add one?
replyContent: Yes, if you press on the category color in the 'Edit Categories' screen, you can change the colour.

content: Two improvement required 1.  Search option shows only date as of now. Time details also required.  2. previous entry is prompted.      Those entry should be stored.      user can add or remove new entry.  Kindly do this.Then this is best apps for log entry and food log entry

A nice looking app. I like how it displays the entire food diary for a day without having to scroll down. One issue though, at the start of a new day it shows everything I've eaten for the previous day on the current day. I have to scroll back through all the previous days and then scroll back to the current day before it clears that. This will get progressively worse the more data you enter as you have to scroll right the way back to before the first day you entered data. Please fix this.

I really like this app! It's perfect for people like me who like lists. I like that you can color code the entries. And that the "titles" can be very long. I don't really use the comment section. I just write what I want in the title section so it shows up. I didn't like its simplicity at first, but now I have an awesome system that works great for me.
I needed a food tracker for gestational diabetes and this app is perfect! I can add my levels to the name of the note and put what foods I ate in the notes section.  Definitely user friendly.

This app is just what I needed to track my eating habits. I can see what I eat and how long it lasts before I eat again. It has also helped me identify foods that trigger eating binges and times of day I am likely to binge. A simple and helpful tool for anyone who eats like I do. 5 stars.
Much better than the free one as I can do new entries on previous days & color code for quick scanninng.

Have used this for years, to track food, medication, exercise, budget, whatever.  The app has just what is needed to do this; enough fields, user-customisation of categories, auto-complete for things you have already entered, and the ability to get it done quickly.  Some apps may have more features around a specific 'type' of data, but then they can't be used for anything else. So it works perfectly as a place to log everything.  In itself, this would have got it 4.stars (which, for me, is very high). The fact that I had an issue, emailed the dev, Geoff (who I had never spoken to before), he got back to me immediately, then trawled through ~2 years of data in my csv export, told me how to work around the issue, and is updating the app to address (even though most people would probably never run into it) is definitely worth the extra star.  If you need a place to simply log and maintain multiple categories of information, definitely give this a go.

It's OK as a basic diary. This works in its favour in some ways as it's the easiest app to quickly add food entries to. However it does need more features such as sub categories and the ability to filter days by star rating so that I can easily see all my bad days.   Currently you can only filter by entry.

This is exactly what I was looking for! I didn't need anything with bells and whistles and a million different options. I wanted something that I could simply track my food without trying to look up calories and serving sizes.  THANK YOU!! Now,  if I could find a way to use the same application for my phone and my tablet without having to retype my entries (depending on which device I'm using at the time), it would be 5 stars. Works great on my Samsung Galaxy S4 and Galaxy Tab 3.
replyContent:
The reason that Food Diary can't sync across devices is so that there aren't any privacy issues with storing additional personal (and potentially medical) information in the cloud. 

The only suggestion I can currently add is that you could use the export/import mechanism to transfer entries between devices.

content: I love this app. I only use it to track food that I eat daily. Very functional and no extra unneeded stuff.

This app is elegantly simple. I can easily track food, activity,  and weight. It is actually nice that it does not have a database so I can enter the food in a way that makes sense to me. As a result I can combine foods rather than having to spend the time to list out every piece and part.
[Edit, it's working now, cheers]  I bought this app through the Google Play store. The payment was accepted, but when I attempt to open the app, I see a message saying that the app is not licenced.

Would be nice if there was a barcode scanner for food entries. Also to have under food entries a customizable checklist to more easily keep up with allergenic ingredients. Also, to have a similar customizable checklist for most common symptoms so I'm not typing everything in everytime.
Clean user interface, great features!
Simple without any useless features like other food log apps. Great.
Nice simple app. I just think it needs a few more bells & whistles to be as useful as I need it to be.

Very simple and functional app, though it could use some upgrades. It is not attractive and it only lets you rate days. It would be much more helpful to be able to rate specific notes and use more input options.
This is a very well thought out app that is simple yet covers everything I want.  It would be great if this could be expanded to a web page for easier viewing and editing at a computer.
Simple and easy to use. Would be 5*if it had a couple more imput options. Other than that, its great
- No month or week view!!! - Not able to attach photos - No settings or customizable preferences
Not a good app. Much too basic

This is a very useful app and saves you from actually having to carry a diary around or only enter your nutritional data when at a computer screen. Easy to use, and I like the different coloured texts for each category.  I would however like to be able to synchronise what enter on my tablet to also appear on my tablets food diary. Correct me if I'm wrong but this doesn't seem possible at the moment. Secondly I think a picture function may be useful to add images sometime when you don't have time to type there and then. Third thing to add would be links to supermarket items eg. Maryland cookies and then it would automatically keep track of all the ingredients for you.

This app is perfect for my needs. I have used it daily for a month now to quickly enter what I have eaten. The app remembers frequently used phrases, which is extremely handy. I contacted the developer with a question and received a helpful, courteous reply the same day. Great app!
Easy to use, can add details about food, health and activity! Perfect!

It's exactly what apps should be easy, quick and efficient! Love it... I would love to see a template come in for common entries I.e. Coffee, I use the description to describe how I take it (sugar, milk, etc)

Should allow text input for time as well as the "scroll" interface.  I'd much rather type "6am" or click into the time field and enter "00" after selecting 6 as my hour.  This makes it incredibly inconvenient to enter things for the previous day.
I was expecting a better done app. I can't sync with a Web page for easier typing and does not have calendar view to see many days at once.

For those who need to track daily food intake, this will help. I have colitis & tracking daily activity is pretty efficient with this app. Color coded categories allow for an easy scan of events. Would have rated 5 stars if it had a "go to today" option. It reopens on a day I have been reviewing, then I have to go day by day to reach the current day.

As an athlete with food intolerance this is great for keeping track of my intake and training and any corresponding symptoms without having to deal with the hassle of entering calories like in other apps which I'm not so concerned about, and I find that tedious and time consuming. If u want just somewhere quick and easy to record what you've eaten and when, and add comments about the food or activity this is the app for you.
Do not be tempted by other inferior apps, this is hands down the best that exists. It doesn't require online access and absolutely no strange permissions included!

I just installed this and am not impressed. I tried to use this app 3 times but each time it got stuck and crashed my phone. I could only get out of it by force rebooting my phone. By the time I had done that, and realized it was the app not my phone, and then found the instructions to get a refund, I was out of the 15 minute time frame. So disappointed that it crashes on me, I really thought it sounded like a great app.
Simply the best.
Needed a food log for my nutritionists assisted diet and this fits the bill perfectly.
This is great app and for the most part fits my needs. 1) I wish there was an optional portion feature. 2) I wish it synced across devices. Otherwise awesome.
Doctor requested I keep a food diary, this has fulfilled my needs perfectly! Tracks food, times, activities, medication - perfect so far. Thanks for a great app!
I needed a simple food diary as part of an intolerance investigation and this app does everything I need very easily. Couldn't have been more perfect for me if I'd spec'd it myself.

Great way to keep track of everyday things. But when clicking on an entry to check notes it shouldn't go directly to an edit screen, it should show everything entered for that entry and have a button to edit if needed.

Enjoy having a simple way to track my dietary habits. Why do some of my entries have an asterisk beside them? Program seems to add them automatically. The export is too clumsy to be useful. Overall a great app...thanks.
Cool app,  with the color codes I can also use it to track weigth and workouts.  Only needs nuberic input for time.
Love the app, so simple to use.    One feature request - The option to "star rate" a day say on 1 - 5 would be good to track "irritable" days.  Thanks for putting the time in on this app :)
I've been looking for an app just like this. And the steady growth of features is encouraging.
This is EXACTLY what I wanted to hunt my food intolerances down.  Do you have suggestions on analyzing the food diary??

Very easy to use and the category customization is excellent! I've already found a food intolerance I didn't know I had. Export tool is useful. Developers, please: (1) Add an "apply to all" option in Preferences>>Edit Categories that can apply category changes to all existing entries, and (2) Add a comment field that can be applied to the entire day/date
.csv export would be nice
i just got this app.  it has a graphic problem - white on white text.....
Simple, effective way to keep track of food related health problems.
